nline access2star  aThough democratic government calls for well-designed and implemented policy, there is surprisingly little expert guidance available for policy makers and politicians. Working for Policy fills that gap, addressing the nature of policy work and offering necessary guidance. The contributors bring together academic and experiential knowledge in their analysis and evaluation of what modern policy makers do in given situations and of how such actions contribute to the policy process. This unique book demonstrates how scholars can help to ensure that policy makers can acquire the skills and knowledge required in governing complex modern societies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDecision making. 0aPolicy sciences. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aColebatch, Hal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColebatch, Hal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGeuijen, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalffman, Willem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHart, Paul 't, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoppe, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoppe, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoppe, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLoeber, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMetze, Tamara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoordegraaf, Mirko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rela